    skos:altLabel "Ampere Turn"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "AmpereTurn"@en ;
    emmo:elucidation """The `ampere-turn` was the MKS unit of magnetomotive force (MMF), represented by a direct current of one ampere flowing in a single-turn loop in a vacuum. "Turns" refers to the winding number of an electrical conductor comprising an inductor. The ampere-turn was replaced by the SI unit, ampere.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/AT" ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "AT" .

