    emmo:elucidation """The cubic inch is a unit of measurement for volume in the Imperial units and United States customary units systems. It is the volume of a cube with each of its three sides being one inch long. The cubic inch and the cubic foot are still used as units of volume in the United States, although the common SI units of volume, the liter, milliliter, and cubic meter, are continually replacing them, especially in manufacturing and high technology. One cubic foot is equal to exactly 1728 cubic inches.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
