    skos:prefLabel "MicroCurie" ;
    emmo:elucidation """Another commonly used measure of radioactivity, the microcurie: 1 μCi = 3.7 × 10 disintegrations per second = 2.22 × 10 disintegrations per minute. A radiotherapy machine may have roughly 1000 Ci of a radioisotope such as caesium-137 or cobalt-60. This quantity of radioactivity can produce serious health effects with only a few minutes of close-range, un-shielded exposure. The typical human body contains roughly 0.1 μCi of naturally occurring potassium-40.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
